================================
=== OPS Web Feeds Plugin
=== Author: MJ Suhonos
=== Contributions: Juan Alperin, Alf Eaton, Alec Smecher
================================

About
-----
This plugin for OPS provides a set of syndication feeds for the latest articles in RSS1.0/RDF and Atom formats. Feed links might be embedded into all pages through a HTML header and are available to all RSS/Atom-aware browsers and aggregators as per standard web specifications.

License
-------
This plugin is licensed under the GNU General Public License v3. See the file COPYING for the complete terms of this license.

System Requirements
-------------------
Same requirements as the OPS core.

Installation
------------
The plugin is included with releases of OPS.

Configuration
------------
The plugin can be configured to display feed links on all server pages, or only the homepage.

Known Issues
------------
- Improperly-formatted (non-RFC2822) email addresses within OPS articles or contact addresses may cause invalid feeds to be generated.
- Articles with no abstract (eg. editorials) will create Atom warnings due to lack of entry:content or entry:summary elements
- Multiple articles with the same publish date/time may create an Atom warning

